UML - Unified Modelling Language
Always create a uml diagram for a system you are building, once you are clear with UML, 90% of the task is done, you just have to implement those in code.
Refer for diagram : https://algomaster.io/learn/lld/class-diagram

1. Building Blocks of Class Diagram
===============================================================================================================================================
Visibility
===============================================================================================================================================
- : private
+ : public
# : protected 
~ : package level

===============================================================================================================================================
Multiplicity
===============================================================================================================================================
Multiplicity specifies the number of instances of one class that can be related to a single instance of another class.

1 (exactly one), 0..1 (zero or one), * (zero or more), 1..* (one or more).

example : 
Email : String [0..1]
Email class depends on String class, and it is related to 0 or 1 instances of String

===============================================================================================================================================
Attribute
===============================================================================================================================================
visibility name: type [multiplicity] = defaultValue

example : 
- name : String
# age : int
+ email : String [0..1] = noemail@gmail.com

email has a public access, string type, that can have 0 or 1 value, with defaults to noemail@gmail.com

===============================================================================================================================================
Method
===============================================================================================================================================
visibility name(parameterList): returnType

example:
+ calculatePrice(int) : int

calculate price is pulically visible, that takes one int argument and return int output

===============================================================================================================================================
Class
===============================================================================================================================================
Composed of attribute and methods

---------------------------------------
|              ClassName               |
---------------------------------------
| - privateField1 : DataType           |
| - privateField2 : DataType           |
| # protectedField : DataType          |
| + publicField : DataType             |
---------------------------------------
| + constructor(param : Type)          |
| + publicMethod(param : Type) : Type  |
| - privateMethod() : Type             |
| # protectedMethod() : Type           |
---------------------------------------

===============================================================================================================================================
Interface
===============================================================================================================================================

<<interface>> is mandatory UML notation
All methods are implicitly public abstract
No instance variables

---------------------------------------
|          <<interface>>               |
|             Flyable                  |
---------------------------------------
| + fly() : void                       |
| + getMaxHeight() : int               |
---------------------------------------

===============================================================================================================================================
Abstract class 
===============================================================================================================================================

<<abstract>> or italic class name
Can contain:
	fields
	constructors
	concrete methods
	abstract methods

---------------------------------------
|         <<abstract>>                 |
|             Bird                     |
---------------------------------------
| # name : String                      |
| # weight : double                    |
---------------------------------------
| + Bird(name : String)                |
| + eat() : void                       |
| + move() : void {abstract}           |
---------------------------------------


